# Worked example of assembly of a plasmid with FastCloneAssist and Pydna

The three sequences below, a1, b and a2 represent a vector sequence a1,2 and and insert sequence b. 
The a1 and a2 are the two parts spanning the origin of a circular sequence.


	     --632bp_PCR_pro_rc--
	     \/                \/
	     /\                /\
	 --a1--                --a2--
	|                            |
	 ----------------------------



	>a1 500 bp
	

	>b 600 bp
	

	>a2 700 bp
	

The FastCloneAssist tool specifies an input with sequences separated by "+" as shown below

Lets replicate this assembly with pydna


>Vect.Primer_F (designed by FastCloneAssist)
CGTTTTGAATCCTCGGTCCCCCTTGTC

>Vect.Primer_R (designed by FastCloneAssist)
TGCCATGTCGAAGTCCATTATAAGCGT

>vector
